            <p class="text-sm -mt-2">Every transaction differs, but most conveyancing matters follow several key operational stages:</p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/5">
                    <h4 class="text-white font-semibold text-base">1. Initial Consultation</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">We begin by understanding the proposed transaction, the parties involved, financing arrangements, commercial objectives, and any potential legal concerns. Early legal advice often prevents significant problems later.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/5">
                    <h4 class="text-white font-semibold text-base">2. Legal Due Diligence</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 mb-2">Due diligence is one of the most important stages of any property transaction. Depending on the transaction, we may conduct:</p>
