            <p>
                Many property disputes arise because purchasers rely solely on information supplied by sellers or estate agents. Proper legal due diligence can identify issues such as forged title documents, fraudulent sellers, pending court disputes, double allocation, multiple competing interests, restrictions registered against title, unpaid land rates, outstanding land rent, invalid succession documentation, missing company approvals, or defective transfers.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">
